Osagie Ize-Iyamu’s running mate, Audu Ganiyu has been disqualified by the Edo State High Court sitting in Benin on Wednesday.  His candidature as the running mate of Ize-Iyamu has been voided by the court after he was found to have presented a false certificate to the Independent National Electoral Commission in the September 19, 2020 governorship election. A member of the Peoples Democratic Party, Kadiri Oshoakhemhe, had in a suit No: B/358/20 filed a case against the APC deputy governorship candidate and two others. Delivering judgment in Benin City, the presiding judge, Justice H.A Courage-Ogbebor, said that Ganiyu presented false information to the Independent National Electoral Commission in his Form EC9. Ganiyu was the running mate of Osagie Ize-Iyamu, the APC governorship candidate in the last governorship election won by Governor Godwin Obaseki of the Peoples Democratic Party. Details later.. Source The Federal High Court in Abuja, on Monday, ordered substituted service of a suit seeking the disqualification of the All Progressives Congress’ governorship candidate in the forthcoming election in Edo State, Osagie Ize-Iyamu, and his running mate, Audu Ganiyu. Justice Taiwo Taiwo, granting the plaintiffs’ application for substituted service, ordered… August 11, 2020 In "Politics" By NELSON DAFE, Benin City Results announced so far in the high takes governorship election of Edo State show that incumbent governor Godwin Obaseki of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) is leading and heading for a comfortable win over his main rival, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu of the All Progressives… September 20, 2020 In "Top Stories" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Senior Advocate of Nigeria (SAN) Chief Wole Olanipeku is leading four other SANS in cases of certificate forgery and perjury instituted against Government Godwin Obaseki of Edo State. The plaintiffs are asking the court to disqualify the governor and his deputy from participating in the September… July 19, 2020 In "News"